{"id":109861,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boris_Berezovsky_(pianist)","text":"Boris Berezovsky (Russian: \u0411\u043E\u0440\u0438\u0301\u0441 \u0412\u0430\u0434\u0438\u0301\u043C\u043E\u0432\u0438\u0447 \u0411\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0437\u043E\u0301\u0432\u0441\u043A\u0438\u0439; born Moscow, 4 January 1969) is a famous Russian pianist. Berezovsky studied at the Moscow Conservatory. In 1988 he became well known in the West when he gave a recital in the Wigmore Hall in London. Two years later he won the Gold Medal at the 1990 International Tchaikovsky Competition in Moscow.\nBoris Berezovsky gives concerts all over the world. He plays concertos with many of the great orchestras including the Royal Concertgebouw Orchestra, New York Philharmonic, Philadelphia Orchestra, Orchestre de la Monnaie, Rotterdam Philharmonic, Danish National Radio Symphony Orchestra, NDR Hamburg, Hessischer Rundfunk, New Japan Philharmonic, City of Birmingham Symphony Orchestra and with conductors such as Kurt Masur, Wolfgang Sawallisch, Vladimir Ashkenazy, Mikhail Pletnev and Antonio Pappano. Berezovsky has also made many recordings.\nBerezovsky has a daughter, Evelyne Berezovsky (born 1991), who is also a pianist. He now lives in Brussels. Boris is an excellent jazz pianist and performs with his trio in Russian clubs.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Russian_language","surface_form":"Russian","offset":18},{"uri":"Moscow","surface_form":"Moscow","offset":64},{"uri":"4_January","surface_form":"4 January","offset":72},{"uri":"1969","surface_form":"1969","offset":82},{"uri":"Russia","surface_form":"Russia","offset":100},{"uri":"Pianist","surface_form":"pianist","offset":108},{"uri":"Moscow_Conservatory","surface_form":"Moscow Conservatory","offset":143},{"uri":"1988","surface_form":"1988","offset":167},{"uri":"Recital","surface_form":"recital","offset":220},{"uri":"Wigmore_Hall","surface_form":"Wigmore Hall","offset":235},{"uri":"London","surface_form":"London","offs